pcaCollisionDetection
Class CollisionDetection

java.lang.Object
  pcaCollisionDetection.CollisionDetection

public class CollisionDetection
extends java.lang.Object

Processing Library. Object that allows collisionDetection of many elements. Elements that are added to the set, are mapped to different grids. Like this it is possible to test a CollisionElement only against elements that lay in its surrounding quadrants of each map and not against all elements on the screen. This reduces the amaunts of tests needed to get all collisions on the screen drastically.

Constructor Detail

CollisionDetection

public CollisionDetection(processing.core.PApplet that_)
Creates and Initialises a new Instance of the CollisionDetection Object. After initialisation CollisionElements can be passed to the Instance. CollisionElements in this list are mapped according to their actionRadius. After mapping the elements, any CollisionElement can then be tested for a collision against this list of Elements.

Parameters:
this - Reference to the actual processing Sketch PApplet.

CollisionDetection

public CollisionDetection(processing.core.PApplet that_,
                          java.util.ArrayList<CollisionElement> elements_)
Creates and Initialises a new Instance of the CollisionDetection Object. After initialisation CollisionElements can be passed to the Instance. CollisionElements in this list are mapped according to their actionRadius. After mapping the elements, any CollisionElement can then be tested for a collision against this list of Elements. All passed elements will be added to the list.

Parameters:
this - Reference to the actual processing Sketch PApplet.
elements - ArrayList of CollisionElements to be added to the CollisionDetecton set.

removeElement

public void removeElement(CollisionElement element)
Removes a CollisionElement from the Set of Elements that is tested and directly removes it from the map. This is only needed if you want to test against the set of elements (without the removed one) during the same frame in which you removed it from the list.

Parameters:
element - CollisionElement that should be removed.

remapElements

public void remapElements()
Maps every element according to its actionRadius to a CollisionMap. This function is called inside the pre() function so before each call of the draw() function. You only need to call this if you want to test an element of the list a second time or if you moved an element and want to test against its new position.

testElement

public void testElement(CollisionElement element,
                        boolean removeElement)
Tests a given CollisionElement against the set of all Mapped elements in this CollisionDetection instance.

Parameters:
element - CollisionElement that will be tested against the set.
removeElement - Boolean default true. If this is set to false the tested Element will not be removed from the maps (if it is contained in one). This will make bulg CollisionTests remarkably slower.
